schema.name: agencies
schema.sql: CREATE TABLE "agencies" (`id` char(36) NOT NULL, `name` varchar(255) NULL, `director_of_client_services` varchar(255) NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`), CONSTRAINT `agencies_director_of_client_services_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`director_of_client_services`) REFERENCES `directus_users` (`id`) ON DELETE SET NULL)

schema.name: clients
schema.sql: CREATE TABLE "clients" (`id` char(36) NOT NULL, `name` varchar(255) NULL, `agency` char(36) NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`), CONSTRAINT `clients_agency_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`agency`) REFERENCES `agencies` (`id`) ON DELETE SET NULL)

schema.name: contacts
schema.sql: CREATE TABLE "contacts" (`id` char(36) NOT NULL, `first_name` varchar(255) NULL, `last_name` varchar(255) NULL, `email` varchar(255) NULL, `title` varchar(255) NULL, `client` char(36) NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`), CONSTRAINT `contacts_client_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`client`) REFERENCES `clients` (`id`) ON DELETE SET NULL)

schema.name: projects
schema.sql: CREATE TABLE "projects" (`id` integer PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT NOT NULL, `name` varchar(255) NULL, `client` char(36) NULL, `type` varchar(255) NULL, CONSTRAINT `projects_client_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`client`) REFERENCES `clients` (`id`) ON DELETE SET NULL)

schema.name: questions
schema.sql: CREATE TABLE "questions" (`id` integer PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT NOT NULL, `user_created` char(36) NULL, `date_created` datetime NULL, `user_updated` char(36) NULL, `date_updated` datetime NULL, `title` varchar(255) null, `type` varchar(255) null, `response` text null, CONSTRAINT `questions_user_created_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`user_created`) REFERENCES `directus_users` (`id`), CONSTRAINT `questions_user_updated_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`user_updated`) REFERENCES `directus_users` (`id`))

schema.name: responses
schema.sql: CREATE TABLE "responses" (`id` integer PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT NOT NULL, `date_created` datetime NULL, `survey` char(36) NULL, `data` json null, CONSTRAINT `responses_survey_foreign` FOREIGN KEY (`survey`) REFERENCES `surveys` (`id`) ON DELETE SET NULL)

schema.name: surveys
schema.sql: CREATE TABLE `surveys` (`id` char(36) not null, primary key (`id`))
